"use strict";(self.webpackChunkdocumentation=self.webpackChunkdocumentation||[]).push([[49],{6323:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"failure-in-localization","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/failure-in-localization","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-09-failure-in-localization.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-09-failure-in-localization.md","title":"Failure in Localization \ud83d\ude1e","description":"I tried, but I couldn\'t get the localization to work. \ud83d\ude13","date":"2025-08-09T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.18,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"failure-in-localization","title":"Failure in Localization \ud83d\ude1e","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Your own structured query language","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/MDQL"}},"content":"I tried, but I couldn\'t get the localization to work. \ud83d\ude13\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nI spent the whole day trying to add an English translation, but no matter what I did or how hard I tried - nothing worked. \ud83d\ude29"},{"id":"MDQL","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/MDQL","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-08-MDQL.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-08-MDQL.md","title":"Your own structured query language","description":"MDQL \u2014 MarkDown Query Language","date":"2025-08-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.91,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"MDQL","title":"Your own structured query language","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Failure in Localization \ud83d\ude1e","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/failure-in-localization"},"nextItem":{"title":"About Hooks","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/hooks-and-paths"}},"content":"MDQL \u2014 MarkDown Query Language\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nIf earlier to get context from a file it was necessary to either look at pre-created tl;dr, or ask a separate agent to compress the context from the file,\\n\\nnow there is a separate query language for querying or changing data in MD files \u2014 **MDQL**.\\n\\n:::info MDQL\\nThis is a language inherited from GraphQL, allowing agents to get and change only the necessary data from Markdown files. This ensures programmatic tl;dr, as well as transparency and control over queries.\\n\\nMDQL optimizes work with a large number of documents, reducing data redundancy and speeding up query processing.\\n\\nBoth reading and writing are supported, which allows not only to retrieve information, but also to automatically update or structure the content.\\n\\n__Example__ of a simple MDQL query:\\n\\n```GraphQL\\n{\\n  file(path: \\"characters/hero.md\\") {\\n    frontmatter {\\n      name\\n      role\\n    }\\n    content(filter: \\"skills\\") {\\n      title\\n      description\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n````\\n\\nThis query will extract only the name, role, and description of skills from the hero file.\\n\\n:::caution This is just an example\\nMDQL is just an idea for now, the implementation will most likely look completely different\\n:::"},{"id":"hooks-and-paths","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/hooks-and-paths","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-08-hooks-and-paths.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-08-hooks-and-paths.md","title":"About Hooks","description":"Hooks for Agent Story Generation","date":"2025-08-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Idea","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/idea","description":"Ideas for the project"},{"inline":false,"label":"Think","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/think","description":"Thoughts and reflections"}],"readingTime":0.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"hooks-and-paths","title":"About Hooks","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["idea","think"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Your own structured query language","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/MDQL"},"nextItem":{"title":"Added a Welcome Page","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-welcome-page"}},"content":"Hooks for Agent Story Generation\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n:::info According to the idea, plot hooks are eternal\\n\\nBecause they have connections at different levels:\\n- Primary - the object itself, which has plot possibilities\\n- Secondary - memories/traces of the object\\n:::\\n\\nAnd if so, it turns out that even if an object is lost, it only means that _the system can introduce a plot line_ to find the object, which is good for the game.\\n\\n---\\n\\nOverall, it turns out that the only way to work with hooks is not to use them and add them, because new plot tropes may open up for us, which will create new events that will make more hooks."},{"id":"added-welcome-page","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-welcome-page","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-07-added-a-welcome-page.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-07-added-a-welcome-page.md","title":"Added a Welcome Page","description":"First step in the project","date":"2025-08-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.04,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"added-welcome-page","title":"Added a Welcome Page","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"About Hooks","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/hooks-and-paths"},"nextItem":{"title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/the-idea-of-agent-stories"}},"content":"[First](/Norchevsky/welcome) step in the project"},{"id":"the-idea-of-agent-stories","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/the-idea-of-agent-stories","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-07-the-idea-of-agent-stories.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-07-the-idea-of-agent-stories.md","title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","description":"How Agents Invent the Future","date":"2025-08-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Idea","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/idea","description":"Ideas for the project"}],"readingTime":0.66,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"the-idea-of-agent-stories","title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["idea"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Added a Welcome Page","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/added-welcome-page"},"nextItem":{"title":"Documentation Begins","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/first-blog-post"}},"content":"How Agents Invent the Future\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nAccording to the idea, worker agents when creating the future must take into account the _present_ and the _past_.\\n\\nThis means they must rely on **their** previous iterations.  \\nThese iterations store not only **what** they did (for example, came up with an event and a way to achieve it),  \\nbut also **what prerequisites** they left for future steps.\\n\\nYes, during generation they can also consider the **context of the whole world**.  \\nTherefore, the formula for generating the future looks something like this:\\n\\n```text\\npast + present + previous iterations + world context = future events\\n```\\n\\n**World context** is everything that agents can additionally introduce into the game while preserving the lore and style,\\nso that something new appears in the story, not just the same thing in a loop."},{"id":"first-blog-post","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/first-blog-post","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-06-first-blog-post.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-06-first-blog-post.md","title":"Documentation Begins","description":"First Steps in Documentation","date":"2025-08-06T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Story","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/story","description":"Talking about something"}],"readingTime":0.13,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"first-blog-post","title":"Documentation Begins","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["story"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"The Idea of Agent Stories","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/the-idea-of-agent-stories"},"nextItem":{"title":"Norchevsky\'s Appearance","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/norchevskys-appearance"}},"content":"First Steps in Documentation\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nToday is the first day of development! \ud83c\udf89  \\nI chose **Docusaurus** because of:\\n\\n- \u2728 Beauty  \\n- \ud83d\udd27 Versatility\\n\\nIt has blogs, documentation, and separate pages!"},{"id":"norchevskys-appearance","metadata":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/norchevskys-appearance","editUrl":"https://github.com/teta42/Norchevsky/edit/main/blog/2025-08-05-norchevskys-appearance.md","source":"@site/i18n/en/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2025-08-05-norchevskys-appearance.md","title":"Norchevsky\'s Appearance","description":"The Chthonic Appearance of Norchevsky","date":"2025-08-05T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Think","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/tags/think","description":"Thoughts and reflections"}],"readingTime":0.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Nicolas Tetha","title":"Localhost CEO, Creator of Norchevsky","url":"https://t.me/Petaurka","page":{"permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/authors/nicolas"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/teta42"},"imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/138377302?v=4","key":"Nicolas"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"norchevskys-appearance","title":"Norchevsky\'s Appearance","authors":["Nicolas"],"tags":["think"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Documentation Begins","permalink":"/Norchevsky/en/blog/first-blog-post"}},"content":"The Chthonic Appearance of Norchevsky\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nHis true appearance is that of a tall, slender humanoid with a wide mouth stretching from ear to ear filled with sharp teeth, and a single large eye in the middle with a pupil like Dio Brando from JoJo\'s Bizarre Adventure.\\n\\nHe is pitch black, like tar, and his body is covered in some kind of tattered cloth. He is entirely black except for the whites of his eye and his gleaming white teeth.\\n\\nOn his back, there\'s a not very tall but very sharp hump at shoulder blade level.\\n\\nLong, sharp fingers.\\n\\nHe himself is kind-hearted and wouldn\'t hurt a fly.\\n\\n---"}]}}')}}]);